```


Kafka Connect is a scalable, fault-tolerant framework for streaming data between Kafka and external systems (databases, object stores, search engines) without writing custom producer/consumer code. Schema Registry manages and enforces schemas for Kafka messages.

### Connect Architecture

```
Source System  →  [Source Connector]  →  Kafka Topic  →  [Sink Connector]  →  Target System
   (MySQL)        (Debezium CDC)         (orders)        (Elasticsearch)      (Search Index)
```

Connectors run as **tasks** inside a Connect worker. Workers can be standalone (single process) or distributed (cluster, recommended for production).

### Running a JDBC Source Connector

```json
{
  "name": "jdbc-source-orders",
  "config": {
    "connector.class": "io.confluent.connect.jdbc.JdbcSourceConnector",
    "connection.url": "jdbc:mysql://db:3306/shop",
    "connection.user": "kafka",
    "connection.password": "secret",
    "table.whitelist": "orders",
    "mode": "timestamp+incrementing",
    "timestamp.column.name": "updated_at",
    "incrementing.column.name": "id",
